Part I

	I believe that smoking is one of the top killers of our time.  My question is why are we still putting ourselves in the same situation over and over again. If we now it will kill us why do we do it.  Everyone know the effects of smoking ends in a deadly outcome.  So why are we being sold something that will only hurt us in the end.  I believe that the only reason smoking is legal is because the government is making way too much money of our addiction.  They are making even more off our medical bills from the effect of smoking. 

	Another point I would like to make is, how is it that the people that don't like smoke and don't want to be around smoke should have to tolerate it.  Shouldn't that be against the law, isn't that a violation of our personal space. It has been proven that even non smokers can die or suffer from lung cancer cause by smoking it is called second hand smoke.  Meaning that you don't even have to be voluntarily smoking and you can still get the deadly outcome of it.  See now to me that just doesn't seem fare.  For example, at SIUC we supposedly have a non smoking policy which no one obeys, people that prefer to smoke are told not to do it in the buildings and only 25 feet away from the buildings but no one obeys these rules. Except they smoke right in front of the door and even in the public restrooms or even in their rooms in these buildings.  If you ask me there really isn't a policy at all.  Something needs to change immediately
